A former Special Adviser to the Governor on Information and Communication Technology, under the administration of Senator Abiola Ajimobi, Niyi Ajao, has died. A close political associate of the deceased who refused to mention his name confirmed the sad need on Wednesday through a telephone interview with a journalist in Ibadan. Mr. Ajao, according to the sources, died in the early hours of Monday. He was in his early 40s. He breathed his last at his residence after a long battle with an undisclosed illness. Niyi Ajao was a young compound chief in Ibadanland, known as Mogaji. He was the Mogaji of Ayegun.